# Next.js Folder Structure Rules (MANDATORY)

## App Router Structure
- **`src/app/`** - Contains ONLY route files (page.tsx, layout.tsx, etc.)
- **`src/screens/`** - Contains ALL page components and screen-level components  
- **`src/components/`** - Contains reusable UI components

## Page Creation Pattern (REQUIRED)
When creating a new page:
1. Create `src/app/[route]/page.tsx` (route handler only)
2. Create `src/screens/[ScreenName]/index.tsx` (actual component)
3. Import screen component into page.tsx

## Example Structure
```
src/
├── app/
│   ├── page.tsx (imports HomeScreen)
│   ├── about/
│   │   └── page.tsx (imports AboutScreen)
│   └── contact/
│       └── page.tsx (imports ContactScreen)
├── screens/
│   ├── Home/
│   │   └── HomeScreens.tsx
│   │   └── index.tsx
│   ├── About/
│   │   └── AboutScreens.tsx
│   │   └── index.tsx
│   └── Contact/
│       └── ContactScreens.tsx
│   │   └── index.tsx
└── components/
    ├── Button/
    │   └── Button.tsx
    │   └── index.tsx
    ├── Header/
    │   └── Header.tsx
    │   └── index.tsx
    ├── Footer/
    │   └── Footer.tsx
    │   └── index.tsx
```

## Page.tsx Template (MANDATORY)
```tsx
import React from 'react'
import [ScreenName] from '#/screens/[ScreenName]'

const page = () => {
  // Route-specific logic only (params, feature flags, etc.)
  return (
    <[ScreenName] />
  )
}

export default page
```

## Screen Component Template (MANDATORY)
```tsx
import React from 'react'

const [ScreenName] = () => {
  return (
    <div>
      {/* Screen content */}
    </div>
  )
}

export default [ScreenName]
```

## index Template
```tsx

export { default } from './componentsName'
```

## Import Paths
- Use `#/screens/[ScreenName]` for screen imports
- Use `#/components/[ComponentName]` for component imports
- Use `#/` as alias for `src/`

## Naming Conventions
- **Pages**: lowercase with hyphens (`about-us`, `contact-form`)
- **Screens**: PascalCase (`AboutUs`, `ContactForm`)
- **Components**: PascalCase (`Button`, `Header`)

## Violation Consequences
- ❌ NO components in app/ folder
- ❌ NO business logic in page.tsx
- ❌ NO direct component creation in page.tsx
- ✅ ONLY route handling in page.tsx
- ✅ ONLY component rendering in page.tsx
- ✅ ALL business logic in screens/

**This structure is MANDATORY for all new pages and components.**
